      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 43 九三</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 43 九三</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九三：壯于頄，有凶。君子夬夬，獨行遇雨，若濡有慍，无咎。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The third NINE, undivided, shows its subject (about to advance) with strong (and determined) looks. There will be evil. (But) the superior man, bent on cutting off (the criminal), will walk alone and encounter the rain, (till he be hated by his proper associates) as if he were contaminated (by the others). (In the end) there will be no blame against him.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
