      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 43 九四</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 43 九四</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九四：臀无膚，其行次且。牽羊悔亡，聞言不信。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fourth NINE, undivided, shows one from whose buttocks the skin has been stripped, and who walks slowly and with difficulty. (If he could act) like. a sheep led (after its companions), occasion for repentance would disappear. But though he hear these words, he will not believe them.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
