      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 43 九五</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九五：莧陸夬夬，中行无咎。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fifth NINE, undivided, shows (the small men like) a bed of purslain, which ought to be uprooted with the utmost determination. (The subject of the line having such determination), his action, in harmony with his central position, will lead to no error or blame.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
